      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Hi all, sorry for the confusion.  I was talking about the declaration of the <code>interface</code> itself. As in <code>public interface Foo</code> vs <code>interface Foo</code>.  The latter is definitely <i>package private</i> in Java 1.8.  I believe that I got confused in reading @rec &#39;s response and didn&#39;t realize they were talking about interface <i>methods</i> only. I confirm that you don&#39;t need the <code>public</code> keyword for interface <i>methods</i> as they seem to be accessible to anyone that has access to the interface."
